ains resolved. The spec says condition-specificity applies to KD/effect/disease hops and explicitly says HOP-2 is contrast-based, not condition-resolved, in `docs/lbd-proposer-spec.md:113-116`."},{"prior_finding_id":"F-005","rationale":"Resolved. `docs/lbd-proposer-spec.md:117-124` requires exact disease filtering and post-filter verdict synthesis, addressing the prior generic-referee disease pass-through risk. The original referee supports only any significant disease after filtering gene and gene_set at `pyzobot_referee.py:249-282`, so the specified override is the right thin adapter."},{"prior_finding_id":"F-006","rationale":"Resolved enough for build. The CSV has 14 non-negative-control disease values, including umbrella rows `autoimmune disease` and `inflammatory bowel disease`, and negative controls are separate (`age-related macular degeneration`, `chronic kidney disease`, `coronary artery disease`). The spec lists the 12 eligible specific diseases plus those two umbrellas as context-only in `docs/lbd-proposer-spec.md:44-53`."},{"prior_finding_id":"F-007","rationale":"Resolved. The hard disjoint gate is replaced with preflight histograms and a ranked novelty penalty in `docs/lbd-proposer-spec.md:72-84`; strict-zero is no longer required to return candidates."},{"prior_finding_id":"F-008","rationale":"Resolved. The spec narrows external evidence to Europe PMC co-mention plus Open Targets for A-C knownness and acknowledges the non-trivial client/cache/mapping work with a revised effort estimate in `docs/lbd-proposer-spec.md:57-70` and `docs/lbd-proposer-spec.md:145-155`."},{"prior_finding_id":"F-009","rationale":"Resolved. `ranked_full` is explicitly banned from seeding A in `docs/lbd-proposer-spec.md:36-38` and only appears as a warning/mitigation, not as an input source."},{"prior_finding_id":"F-010","rationale":"Resolved. The artifact itself was rewritten and now carries the accepted corrections in the executable build sections, not just in debate prose: A sources at `docs/lbd-proposer-spec.md:28-38`, B scope at `39-43`, C eligibility at `44-53`, ranked novelty at `72-84`, adapter contract at `109-124`, and revised effort at `145-155`."},{"prior_finding_id":"F-011","rationale":"Resolved. The spec closes the row-level answer leak by banning `pyzobot_referee_ranked_full.csv` as an A seed in `docs/lbd-proposer-spec.md:36-38` and restates the generative rationale in `docs/lbd-proposer-spec.md:132-135`: A comes from raw KD/DE, novelty from external literature, and the referee runs after generation."},{"prior_finding_id":"F-012","rationale":"Resolved. `docs/lbd-proposer-spec.md:117-124` defines exact-C semantics before final verdict synthesis: filter `t3_exploded` by `gene==A_gene`, `disease==C_disease`, and `gene_set==downstream_<condition>`, support only on `p_adj_fdr < 0.05`, otherwise refute for C after upstream pass. This matches the available columns in `pyzobot_referee.py:70-74` and fixes the generic HOP-3 behavior at `pyzobot_referee.py:249-282`."}],"new_findings":[],"convergence_status":"converged","convergence_sanding_warning":null,"recommended_next_question":"Before building, pin the 12 eligible disease-to-EFO mappings and Th1/Th2 keyword map, then run the mandatory novelty preflight histogram."}
