thesis after exact-C HOP-3, addressing the old generic disease pass-through."},{"prior_finding_id":"F-006","rationale":"Resolved for implementation. The CSV has 14 non-negative-control disease values, including umbrella rows `autoimmune disease` and `inflammatory bowel disease`; the spec lists those as context-only and uses 12 eligible C claims at `docs/lbd-proposer-spec.md:44` and `docs/lbd-proposer-spec.md:53`."},{"prior_finding_id":"F-007","rationale":"Resolved. The hard disjoint gate is replaced by preflight histograms and a ranked novelty penalty in `docs/lbd-proposer-spec.md:72`."},{"prior_finding_id":"F-008","rationale":"Resolved. The spec narrows API scope to Europe PMC plus Open Targets and revises effort to ~1–1.5 days in `docs/lbd-proposer-spec.md:57` and `docs/lbd-proposer-spec.md:150`."},{"prior_finding_id":"F-009","rationale":"Resolved. `ranked_full` is explicitly banned from A seeding in `docs/lbd-proposer-spec.md:36`."},{"prior_finding_id":"F-010","rationale":"Resolved. The artifact itself now contains the accepted fixes across A/B/C source definitions, novelty ranking, exact-C adapter, and effort estimate."},{"prior_finding_id":"F-011","rationale":"Resolved. The answer leak is closed by banning `pyzobot_referee_ranked_full.csv` from seeding and by making the generative rationale explicit in `docs/lbd-proposer-spec.md:132`."},{"prior_finding_id":"F-012","rationale":"Resolved. Exact-C HOP-3 semantics are specified at `docs/lbd-proposer-spec.md:117` and match the available `t3_exploded` columns in `pyzobot_referee.py:70`; the original generic HOP-3 behavior at `pyzobot_referee.py:249` is correctly overridden by the adapter."}],"new_findings":[],"convergence_status":"converged","convergence_sanding_warning":null,"recommended_next_question":"Before building, pin the 12 eligible disease-to-EFO mappings and Th1/Th2 keyword map, then run the mandatory novelty preflight histogram."}
